  "description": "The Constructive Collision recipe with prismatic refraction added — proc3=Wavefolder activates on the merged signal, catching the collision's harmonic peaks and folding them into spectral complexity. Pulse src1 (PW=0.6, slightly wider) against Saw src2 at +4 semitones. proc1=LP (2200 Hz, reso=0.32) and proc2=LP (780 Hz, reso=0.42) define the collision zone; proc3=Wavefolder at 3800 Hz creates prismatic brightness from the fold. fmDepth=0.25 adds active harmonic entanglement. CHARACTER macro 0.28 positions it warm-but-active. All 4 mods: Env->proc1Cutoff, LFO->WavetablePos, Velocity->FilterReso, Aftertouch->proc3Cutoff (live fold depth).",
